21:11.037 --> 21:15.542
[men continue
soulful singing]

21:28.488 --> 21:30.557
- THANK YOU.
- YES, SIR.

21:30.590 --> 21:31.558
- NAME'S BOHANNON.

21:31.591 --> 21:33.726
- YES, SIR.

21:33.760 --> 21:35.428
YES, SIR.

21:40.733 --> 21:42.569
- AH.

21:46.906 --> 21:50.610
ANY YOU ALL EVER BEEN
CHASED BY A BLOODHOUND?

21:50.643 --> 21:52.679
- WE FAMILIAR.
- YEAH, WELL,

21:52.712 --> 21:55.715
ON SHERMAN'S MARCH TO THE SEA,
HE TOLD HIS MEN,

21:55.748 --> 21:57.717
HE SAID, "YOU COME ACROSS
ANY BLOODHOUNDS,

21:57.750 --> 21:58.718
YOU SHOOT 'EM," RIGHT?

21:58.751 --> 22:00.487
SO, THEY GET TO SAVANNAH.

22:00.520 --> 22:02.088
AND THIS REAL GREEN PRIVATE,
HE'S WALKIN' DOWN THE STREET

22:02.121 --> 22:03.956
AND HE SEES THIS LADY
WALKING WITH A POODLE.

22:03.990 --> 22:05.492
YOU KNOW, BOWS IN ITS HAIR
AND EVERYTHING.

22:05.525 --> 22:06.626
ONE LOOK AT THE POODLE,
PULLS OUT HIS GUN.

22:06.659 --> 22:08.094
[imitates gunshot]
RIGHT IN THE HEAD.

22:08.127 --> 22:09.629
SHERMAN COMES
RUNNIN' UP TO HIM,

22:09.662 --> 22:11.431
SAYS "SON, WHY'D YOU KILL
THAT POODLE?"

22:11.464 --> 22:13.433
AND THE PRIVATE SAYS
"SIR, WELL,

22:13.466 --> 22:16.403
ON ACCOUNT OF YOU--YOU NEVER
WHAT THEY'RE GONNA GROW INTO."

22:23.643 --> 22:25.578
[laughter]

22:25.612 --> 22:28.681
- COME ON.

22:28.715 --> 22:30.483
- WHAT'S A POODLE?

22:30.517 --> 22:32.585
[laughter]

22:40.527 --> 22:42.862
- THAT'LL BE $9.00 AND 23¢.

22:46.799 --> 22:48.601
WE TAKE CASH OR SCRIP.

22:48.635 --> 22:49.836
- CAN I GET CREDIT?

22:49.869 --> 22:51.704
- NO CREDIT.

22:51.738 --> 22:53.540
IF YOU AIN'T GOT
CASH NOR SCRIP,

22:53.573 --> 22:56.175
I CAN'T SELL YOU NOTHIN'.

22:56.208 --> 22:58.845
- BUT I NEED THESE THINGS.

22:58.878 --> 23:01.848
- AND I GOT
A BUSINESS TO RUN.

23:01.881 --> 23:03.683
- THAT'S ALL RIGHT,
MR. ADLER.

23:03.716 --> 23:07.119
I'LL TAKE CARE OF
MRS. BOHANNON'S SUNDRIES TODAY.

23:10.056 --> 23:13.125
I'M SURE MR. BOHANNON
IS GOOD FOR IT.

23:13.159 --> 23:15.528
- YES, SIR,
MR. CAMPBELL.

23:15.562 --> 23:16.529
WHATEVER YOU SAY.

23:46.859 --> 23:48.595
- I'MA RAISE YA.

23:48.628 --> 23:50.663
- ALL RIGHT, YOUNG LADY.

23:50.697 --> 23:51.764
CALL.

24:10.550 --> 24:12.785
- FULL HOUSE.

24:12.819 --> 24:17.590
QUEENS OVER 10s.

24:17.624 --> 24:18.725
[laughs]

24:18.758 --> 24:21.728
- WHOA WHOA WHOA
WHOA WHOA, EASY NOW.

24:21.761 --> 24:23.195
NOT SO FAST.

24:23.229 --> 24:28.568
YOU KNOW, IT REALLY IS HARD
TO BEAT A LADY.

24:28.601 --> 24:29.902
UNLESS YOU'RE A KING.

24:38.845 --> 24:41.914
- BUT HOW DID--
HOW'D YOU DO THAT?

24:41.948 --> 24:43.916
NO, THAT AIN'T RIGHT.

24:43.950 --> 24:46.853
- DON'T CRY.
IT'S ONLY MONEY.

25:02.702 --> 25:05.004
- HOWDY, MA'AM.

25:25.658 --> 25:28.160
- I DON'T WANT
MY MONEY BACK, I SWEAR.

25:28.194 --> 25:30.797
I JUST WANT TO KNOW
HOW YOU CHEATED ME.

25:40.006 --> 25:41.841
- YOU CHEATED YOURSELF,
WOMAN,

25:41.874 --> 25:44.811
BY SITTIN' DOWN AT A TABLE
WITH THE LIKES OF ME.

25:44.844 --> 25:47.346
NOW, YOU ARE
EITHER DESPERATE,

25:47.379 --> 25:49.782
GREEDY,

25:49.816 --> 25:52.318
OR STUPID.

25:52.351 --> 25:53.853
- I'M JUST DESPERATE.

25:53.886 --> 25:56.856
AND STUPID.

25:56.889 --> 25:58.625
AND I NEED TO KNOW
HOW YOU DID IT.

25:58.658 --> 26:00.860
- THAT'S DANGEROUS KNOWLEDGE

26:00.893 --> 26:02.361
FOR SOMEONE WHO DON'T KNOW
HOW TO USE IT.

26:02.394 --> 26:04.296
- I KNOW HOW TO USE IT.

26:11.037 --> 26:12.739
- IT'S ALL IN THE GRIP.

26:12.772 --> 26:16.709
NOW, SAY IF
SOMEONE WERE TO CHEAT...

26:16.743 --> 26:19.011
THUMB, FINGERTIPS.

26:19.045 --> 26:21.848
THUMB, FINGERTIPS.

26:28.020 --> 26:30.857
- TEACH ME.

26:30.890 --> 26:34.827
- WHAT TOOK ME YEARS
TO PERFECT?

26:34.861 --> 26:36.763
I AIN'T STUPID.

26:38.798 --> 26:40.900
- I'LL MAKE IT
WORTH YOUR WHILE.

27:04.123 --> 27:05.892
- DOUBLE THE POWDER
ON THOSE CHARGES.

27:05.925 --> 27:07.827
- YES, SIR.

27:09.729 --> 27:12.198
- THAT MUCH POWDER'S LIKELY
TO GET US ALL KILLED.

27:12.231 --> 27:14.934
- BOSS MAN DECIDE
HOW MUCH POWDER WE USE.

27:14.967 --> 27:18.137
YOU AIN'T BOSS MAN
NO MORE.

27:24.944 --> 27:28.180
- MR. DELANEY.

27:28.214 --> 27:29.916
THAT ROCK?
[roc shatters, clatters]

27:29.949 --> 27:31.450
IT'S SHALE.

27:31.483 --> 27:34.086
WHERE THERE'S SHALE,
THERE'S METHANE.

27:34.120 --> 27:36.088
YOU DOUBLE THAT POWDER,

27:36.122 --> 27:37.924
SHRAPNEL'S LIKELY TO KILL
EVERY MAN

27:37.957 --> 27:40.927
WITHIN ABOUT A HUNDRED YARDS
OF THAT WALL RIGHT THERE.

27:46.432 --> 27:47.934
- GET BACK TO WORK,
BOHANNON.

27:47.967 --> 27:49.969
I WANT YOUR ADVICE,
I'LL ASK FOR IT.

27:50.002 --> 27:52.004
- ALL RIGHT.
TURN THEM TABLES OVER,

27:52.038 --> 27:53.740
GET BEHIND 'EM
BEFORE THAT THING BLOWS.

27:56.876 --> 27:58.110
- YOU KNOW
I AIN'T ONE TO COME

27:58.144 --> 27:59.145
BETWEEN TWO FEUDIN'
WHITE MEN.

27:59.178 --> 28:01.013
- YOU DON'T WANT TO DIE,
NEITHER.

28:05.051 --> 28:07.053
- DO IT!
TURN 'EM OVER!

28:12.859 --> 28:14.493
- LIGHT THOSE FUSES.

28:14.526 --> 28:17.096
[men shouting orders
in background]

28:34.513 --> 28:38.450
- MR. BOHANNON, YOU ABOUT
TO GET YOUR JOB BACK.

28:43.990 --> 28:44.957
- SHIT!

28:53.032 --> 28:57.804
[boom]

28:59.538 --> 29:02.074
[horses neigh]

29:03.209 --> 29:07.046
[rocks thudding,
horses neighing]

29:11.951 --> 29:16.055
[horse neighs]

29:39.211 --> 29:40.546
[gunshot]

29:49.221 --> 29:51.023
- WHAT DO YOU WANT?

29:54.360 --> 29:57.563
- I DIDN'T KNOW ELAM'D
GONE LOOKIN' FOR ME.

29:57.596 --> 29:59.065
- YOU SHOULDA KNOWN
YOU'D DISAPPEAR LIKE THAT,

29:59.098 --> 30:01.200
HE'S GONNA COME LOOKIN'.

30:01.233 --> 30:03.602
- I DIDN'T DISAPPEAR.
I WAS TOOK.

30:03.635 --> 30:07.173
BY ARMED MEN
AGAINST MY WILL.

30:11.010 --> 30:13.212
- BUT BY THEN
HE WASN'T LISTENIN' TO ME.

30:13.245 --> 30:15.247
I'VE BEEN HAVIN' DREAMS...

30:15.281 --> 30:17.283
ABOUT ELAM.

30:17.316 --> 30:22.288
NOT EVERY NIGHT,
BUT MOST NIGHTS.

30:22.321 --> 30:24.256
I'M IN A BIG CITY
SOMEWHERES.

30:24.290 --> 30:26.058
CHICAGO.

30:26.092 --> 30:27.626
NEW YORK.

30:27.659 --> 30:28.594
I'M LOST.

30:28.627 --> 30:30.062
WALKIN' THE STREETS.

30:30.096 --> 30:33.132
LOOKIN' INTO PEOPLES' HOMES.

30:33.165 --> 30:35.234
THEIR NICE WARM WINDOWS.

30:35.267 --> 30:37.003
I'M ON THE OUTSIDE.

30:37.036 --> 30:39.171
ALWAYS ON THE OUTSIDE.

30:39.205 --> 30:41.073
EVERYONE'S AFRAID OF ME.

30:41.107 --> 30:43.109
[thunder rumbles]

30:43.142 --> 30:46.278
I THINK IT'S
'CAUSE OF MY TATTOO.

30:46.312 --> 30:50.649
AND THEN I REALIZE...

30:50.682 --> 30:53.652
THAT'S NOT WHAT IT IS.

30:53.685 --> 30:57.256
I SEE MY REFLECTION.

30:57.289 --> 31:00.126
I'M NOT ME ANYMORE.

31:00.159 --> 31:01.961
I'M A BEAR,

31:01.994 --> 31:05.564
AND I'M LOOKIN' FOR ELAM.

31:05.597 --> 31:09.001
- THEMS IS JUST DREAMS, EVA.

31:11.203 --> 31:14.173
THEY DON'T MEAN NOTHIN'.

31:14.206 --> 31:17.209
- HE CONSIDERED YOU
A FRIEND, MR. BOHANNON.

31:17.243 --> 31:19.311
I EXPECT THAT MIGHT
MEAN SOMETHIN' TO YA,

31:19.345 --> 31:23.115
SINCE I KNOW YOU
AIN'T HAD MANY.

31:23.149 --> 31:25.017
- WELL...

31:25.051 --> 31:26.118
ONE FEWER NOW.

31:38.330 --> 31:42.068
- MR. THOMAS DURANT
OF THE UNION PACIFIC

31:42.101 --> 31:44.203
IS NOT THE FIRST PERSON
WE'VE RUN INTO

31:44.236 --> 31:46.305
WHO DIDN'T SEE THINGS
MY WAY.

31:46.338 --> 31:47.206
- NO, SIR.
[woman screams]

31:47.239 --> 31:48.374
- COME HERE!

31:51.210 --> 31:55.714
- IF PEOPLE BELIEVE ANY ONE
OF THEM IS ABOVE THE LAW,

31:55.747 --> 31:59.151
THERE WILL BE NO LAW.

31:59.185 --> 32:01.187
- DURANT?

32:01.220 --> 32:04.723
- I'D LIKE TO ASK JUDGE WEBBER
HIS OPINION ON A REMEDY.

32:04.756 --> 32:06.558
THIS HOUR, YOU'RE LIKELY
TO FIND HIM

32:06.592 --> 32:11.197
AT THE FARO TABLES
OR THE WHOREHOUSE.

32:11.230 --> 32:13.232
- YES, SIR.

32:14.266 --> 32:16.202
[woman whimpering]
- HEY!

32:16.235 --> 32:19.238
[man shouting]

32:19.271 --> 32:21.307
- GET OFF!
GET OFF!

32:31.750 --> 32:34.420
[baby fussing]

32:36.322 --> 32:39.291
- HOW WAS YOUR DAY,
HUSBAND?

32:39.325 --> 32:41.760
- IT WAS FINE.

32:41.793 --> 32:42.761
YOURS?

32:42.794 --> 32:47.333
- JUST FINE.

32:47.366 --> 32:50.269
[knocking]
- MR. BOHANNON.

32:50.302 --> 32:54.406
YOU IN THERE?

32:58.310 --> 33:01.113
MR. BOHANNON.

33:01.147 --> 33:02.714
GOVERNOR CAMPBELL.

33:05.417 --> 33:07.419
WHY, IT'S NICE TO SEE
YOU AGAIN, MRS. BOHANNON.

33:07.453 --> 33:08.754
- YOU GOT SOMETHIN'
TO SAY TO MY WIFE, SON,

33:08.787 --> 33:10.056
YOU TALK TO ME.

33:10.089 --> 33:12.791
- I BOUGHT HER
A MEAL IS ALL.

33:12.824 --> 33:17.296
HOW YOU ENJOYIN' IT?

33:17.329 --> 33:21.367
- I CAN BUY MY OWN MEALS.

33:21.400 --> 33:27.306
- YOU HANDLED YOURSELF MIGHTILY
WITH MY MEN YESTERDAY.

33:27.339 --> 33:30.276
- LIKE I TOLD 'EM,
I AIN'T LOOKIN' FOR TROUBLE.

33:30.309 --> 33:32.144
Y'ALL HAVE A GOOD NIGHT.

33:32.178 --> 33:37.816
- GENERAL GRANT HOLDS YOU
IN HIGH REGARD, MR. BOHANNON.

33:37.849 --> 33:39.385
- WHAT DO YOU WANT?

33:39.418 --> 33:43.255
- A MAN OF YOUR STATURE
LIVIN' AMONGST THE, UH...

33:43.289 --> 33:44.390
- NEGROS?

33:44.423 --> 33:47.559
- FREEDMEN.
[man snickers]

33:47.593 --> 33:50.429
NOW, YOU DON'T HAVE TO LIVE
IN SQUALOR, MR. BOHANNON.

33:50.462 --> 33:52.798
YOU WORK FOR ME.
I'LL PAY YOU A DECENT WAGE.

33:52.831 --> 33:54.466
- I ALREADY GOT A JOB.

33:54.500 --> 33:56.768
- I'LL PAY YOU THREE TIMES
WHAT YOU MAKE LAYIN' RAIL.

33:56.802 --> 34:00.139
AND I'LL HELP YOU BUILD A HOUSE
FOR YOUR FAMILY.

34:00.172 --> 34:04.210
UNTIL THEN, ALLOW ME TO ENGAGE
A ROOM FOR YOU AT THE HOTEL.

34:04.243 --> 34:06.145
HOT BATH, WARM BED.

34:06.178 --> 34:09.381
YOU COULD BE THERE TONIGHT,
MRS. BOHANNON.

34:09.415 --> 34:12.318
- [laughs]

34:12.351 --> 34:15.287
WORK FOR A CARPETBAGGER?

34:15.321 --> 34:17.489
[chuckles]

34:17.523 --> 34:19.325
NOT A CHANCE IN A HELL.

34:25.564 --> 34:29.501
- THE FREEDMEN'S BUREAU, SIR,
IS BUT ONE LEGACY

34:29.535 --> 34:33.372
OF RECONSTRUCTION I BELIEVE
I SHALL BE REMEMBERED FOR.

34:33.405 --> 34:34.373
AND FONDLY.

34:34.406 --> 34:39.345
SHOULD YOU CHANGE YOUR MIND.

34:52.258 --> 34:54.493
- BY MY COUNT,
THAT'S TWO GOOD JOBS

34:54.526 --> 34:58.397
THAT YOU'VE TURNED DOWN
SINCE WE GOT HERE.

34:58.430 --> 35:01.533
WHAT'RE WE MEANT
TO DO THEN?

35:01.567 --> 35:02.601
[silverware clatters]

35:08.374 --> 35:09.508
- NAOMI...

35:09.541 --> 35:11.277
EVERYTHING I DONE...

35:11.310 --> 35:15.514
ALL THE DEATH AND DESTRUCTION
I PUT MY HAND TO

35:15.547 --> 35:18.884
AND WAS PUT TO ME--

35:18.917 --> 35:23.689
ALL THAT IS FOR NAUGHT
IF I DON'T FINISH THIS ROAD.

35:36.968 --> 35:40.272
- MR. BOHANNON.

35:40.306 --> 35:41.440
- HMM.

35:41.473 --> 35:44.576
SURPRISED YOU'RE STILL HERE.

35:44.610 --> 35:48.314
- LIKEWISE.

35:48.347 --> 35:50.582
- AH.

35:50.616 --> 35:52.951
SOMETHIN' ABOUT THE PLACE.

35:52.984 --> 35:54.853
- THE CUISINE, NO DOUBT.

35:54.886 --> 35:55.921
- THOUGHT YOU WOULD HAVE
HIGHTAILED IT

35:55.954 --> 35:58.224
BACK TO NEW YORK
BY NOW.

35:58.257 --> 35:59.625
- STORY KEEPS ME HERE.

35:59.658 --> 36:01.460
- MM...

36:01.493 --> 36:02.461
CAREFUL IT DON'T KILL YA.

36:02.494 --> 36:04.230
- HASN'T KILLED YOU.

36:04.263 --> 36:05.497
- YET.

36:05.531 --> 36:07.333
- I HEAR YOU GOT MARRIED.

36:07.366 --> 36:09.401
- YEAH.

36:09.435 --> 36:12.471
NICE MORMON GIRL.

36:12.504 --> 36:14.973
- I'M INTERESTED
IN YOUR STORY, MR. BOHANNON.

36:15.006 --> 36:16.642
MY READERS WILL BE
AS WELL.

36:16.675 --> 36:19.345
- [scoffs]

36:19.378 --> 36:21.447
AIN'T A STORY,
MISS ELLISON.

36:21.480 --> 36:23.915
JUST A LIFE.

36:23.949 --> 36:26.918
IT'S MINE TO LIVE,
NOBODY'S TO READ ABOUT.

36:35.461 --> 36:37.496
- OH, I...

36:37.529 --> 36:39.631
SORRY TO INTERRUPT
YOUR SUPPER.

36:39.665 --> 36:43.502
THOUGHT I SHOULD
COME BY AND SAY HOWDY.

36:43.535 --> 36:45.271
HEY.

36:47.373 --> 36:48.607
- WE THOUGHT YOU WERE DEAD.

36:48.640 --> 36:50.509
- HUH?

36:50.542 --> 36:53.479
WHY'D YOU THINK THAT?

36:53.512 --> 36:57.516
- YOU WOULD HAVE
COME BACK OTHERWISE.

36:57.549 --> 36:59.351
- WHY DON'T YOU
GO WAIT OUTSIDE, BOY.

36:59.385 --> 37:00.519
GO ON.

37:06.625 --> 37:10.662
- EZRA HAS MISSED YOU,
MR. BOHANNON.

37:10.696 --> 37:12.964
HE GRIEVED FOR YOU.

37:17.503 --> 37:19.571
AS DID I.

37:19.605 --> 37:23.041
- YOU DONE RIGHT BY HIM.
HE'S GROWIN' UP TALL.

37:23.074 --> 37:24.976
- YES.

37:28.714 --> 37:32.551
WE'RE OUR OWN
LITTLE FAMILY NOW.

37:32.584 --> 37:35.053
THE TWO OF US.

37:35.086 --> 37:36.822
- RUTH--

37:46.532 --> 37:47.699
I'M SORRY.

37:51.470 --> 37:55.674
- NOW YOU'RE BACK.

37:55.707 --> 37:57.609
WITH A NEW WIFE
AND CHILD.

38:00.111 --> 38:01.647
I'M SURE AS THE RAILROAD
STARTS MOVING,

38:01.680 --> 38:04.983
YOU'LL BE MOVING
WITH IT.

38:05.016 --> 38:08.554
I HAVE MY CHURCH
TO LOOK AFTER.

38:08.587 --> 38:12.524
AND THE BOY.

38:12.558 --> 38:14.560
WE'LL BE STAYING HERE.

38:16.628 --> 38:19.465
- I COME TO ASK A FAVOR.

38:22.634 --> 38:25.371
- I DON'T THINK
I CAN HELP YOU.

38:28.073 --> 38:32.644
- NAOMI AND MY BOY,
WILLIAM...

38:32.678 --> 38:36.848
WHEN I'M OUT IN THE CUT,
THEY'RE HERE ALL ALONE.

38:39.718 --> 38:41.920
I KNOW HOW YOU FEEL.

38:44.656 --> 38:47.125
ABOUT MORMONS.

38:47.158 --> 38:49.127
I WAS HOPIN' YOU COULD FIND
IT IN YOUR HEART

38:49.160 --> 38:51.129
TO LEND A HAND.

38:51.162 --> 38:54.633
IF NEED BE.

38:54.666 --> 38:57.503
- I HAVE BUILT THE WALLS
OF MY CHURCH TO BE A STRONGHOLD

38:57.536 --> 38:59.505
FOR THE NEEDY,
MR. BOHANNON.

38:59.538 --> 39:01.740
SHOULD YOUR WIFE AND CHILD
EVER FIND THEMSELVES

39:01.773 --> 39:03.709
AT MY DOOR,

39:03.742 --> 39:06.745
THEY, LIKE EVERYONE ELSE
IN THIS TOWN,

39:06.778 --> 39:08.680
WILL FIND IT OPEN.

39:21.660 --> 39:25.096
- [exhales]

39:25.130 --> 39:27.132
[grunts, sniffs]

39:28.800 --> 39:32.671
YOU KNOW, AIN'T NONE
OF THIS YOUR FAULT, SON.

39:32.704 --> 39:35.173
- YOU TRADED YOURSELF
FOR ME.

39:35.206 --> 39:37.543
- [chuckles]

39:37.576 --> 39:39.144
COME ON.

39:39.177 --> 39:42.180
YOU WOULD HAVE
DONE THE SAME.

39:42.213 --> 39:47.118
- ANYWAYS,
THANK YOU.

39:54.760 --> 39:57.696
- YOU'RE WELCOME.

39:57.729 --> 40:02.100
- * AND HE WALKS WITH ME

40:02.133 --> 40:05.704
* AND HE TALKS WITH ME

40:05.737 --> 40:12.210
* AND HE TELLS ME
I AM HIS OWN *

40:12.243 --> 40:15.681
* AND THE JOY WE SHARE

40:15.714 --> 40:21.753
* AS WE TARRY THERE

40:21.787 --> 40:29.528
* NO OTHER HAS EVER KNOWN

40:32.998 --> 40:36.067
- THE DEFROCKED CHIEF ENGINEER'S
RETURN TO CHEYENNE

40:36.101 --> 40:39.738
MEANS ANOTHER ACTOR
HAS ENTERED THE PLAY,

40:39.771 --> 40:41.940
ALREADY HALF FINISHED.

40:43.775 --> 40:45.911
WITH THE BOMBASTIC DREAMER,

40:45.944 --> 40:50.716
HIS LEGACY DEPENDING
ON COMPLETING THIS ROAD.

40:50.749 --> 40:53.151
AND THE CARPETBAGGING
BUREAUCRAT,

40:53.184 --> 40:56.187
TASKED WITH BRINGING
CIVILIZATION TO A LAND

40:56.221 --> 41:00.726
THAT, JUST YESTERDAY,
BOASTED WILD AND FREE.

41:00.759 --> 41:05.263
CULLEN BOHANNON, FOR REASONS
THIS REPORTER HAS YET TO DIVINE,

41:05.296 --> 41:09.735
SEEMS DETERMINED
TO SEE THIS ROAD THROUGH.

41:09.768 --> 41:14.272
WHETHER HE DOES IT
AS LABORER OR BOSS,

41:14.305 --> 41:16.808
ALIVE OR DEAD,

41:16.842 --> 41:20.245
ONLY TIME WILL TELL,
DEAR READER.

41:20.278 --> 41:22.848
ONLY TIME WILL TELL.

41:30.589 --> 41:32.223
- [grunts]

41:32.257 --> 41:35.561
[He Walks with Me
continues]

41:35.594 --> 41:40.599
*

41:53.244 --> 41:59.785
- * HE WALKS WITH ME
AND HE TALKS WITH ME *

41:59.818 --> 42:06.157
* AND HE TELLS ME
I AM HIS OWN *

42:06.191 --> 42:13.899
* AND THE JOY WE SHARE
AS WE TARRY THERE *

